list.item:
Metformin hydrochloride extended-release tablets are contraindicated in patients with an eGFR less than 30 mL/min/1.73 m2 [see 
                                 Contraindications (4)
                              ].

tr.td:
                                   Cationic drugs eliminated by renal tubular secretion may reduce metformin elimination

[See Warnings and Precautions (5.1) and Drug Interactions (7).
                                   ]
